  "summary": "Reverse shell to hardcoded attacker host on library use",
  "details": "internallib_v234 exports a single function command() in index.js that spawns a Python one-liner via child_process.exec. The payload opens a TCP socket to hardcoded RHOST=10.0.74.133 RPORT=13337, duplicates stdio onto the socket, and calls pty.spawn(\"/bin/sh\"), handing an interactive shell on the installer's machine to the remote host. A bundled consumer script (check.js) invokes command() so the reverse shell fires as soon as that entry is loaded. The package name mimics an internal-library convention and declares itself as its own dependency, consistent with a dependency-confusion lure targeting private-registry names via public npm resolution.",
